# Latency Investigation Rules (STRICT)

> Authority: `restaurant-voice-agent.mdc`. This file supplements, does not override.

## Investigation Protocol

When investigating a latency concern, follow this protocol in order:

### 1. Measure First, Conclude Second
- Query the Supabase calls table for per-turn latency data
- Compare identical question types (FAQ, order, reservation) across time periods
- DO NOT rely on manual observation or "feels slower" — use numbers

### 2. Compare Like-with-Like
- Same intent type (FAQ vs FAQ, order vs order)
- Same turn position (Turn 1 cold-start vs Turn 2+ warm)
- Account for conversation length changes (more turns = longer total, not per-turn regression)

### 3. Check for Confounding Factors
- Longer conversations (more re-asks = more turns) inflate total call time
- Safety net activations (re-asks instead of dumps) add turns
- GCP-side variance (LLM API response time jitter)
- Any recently deployed changes touching max_tokens, timeouts, or phrasing

### 4. Verify Existing Optimizations Are Active
- Prompt caching (`cache_control` blocks) — check for `cache_creation`/`cache_read` in logs
- max_tokens limits — verify no unexpected increase
- Timeout settings — verify `SAILLY_PHRASING_TIMEOUT` and `SAILLY_GROUNDING_TIMEOUT`

### 5. Baseline Reference (as of Jun 21, 2026)

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| FAQ per-turn (P50) | 3.8s |
| FAQ per-turn (P95) | 5.0s |
| Order per-turn (P50) | 2.2s |
| Non-FAQ per-turn (avg) | 2.4s |
| Turn 1 cold-start | 2.0-3.7s |
| Turn 2+ warm | 0.1-0.25s (FSM-only) / 2.0-4.5s (LLM) |
| Industry target (P50 e2e) | <800ms |
| Sailly target (P95 FAQ) | <3.0s |

## Optimization Priority (in order)

| # | Optimization | Est. gain | Effort |
|---|-------------|-----------|--------|
| TTS-4 | Pre-render static phrases (greetings, confirmations, farewells) | 300-800ms cold-start | ~30 LOC + S3 bucket |
| TTS-3 | WebSocket pre-warm at call start | 100-400ms per call | ~15 LOC |
| TTS-7 | Switch to OGG_OPUS output format | 30-100ms | 1 config line |
| TTS-8 | Disable proxy buffering on TTS endpoint | 50-200ms | 3 nginx lines |
| TTS-2 | Sentence-boundary LLM->TTS streaming | 200-500ms perceived | ~200 LOC refactor |

## Hard Stops

| Condition | Verdict |
|-----------|---------|
| Claiming latency increase without DB query | **BLOCKED** — measure first |
| Optimizing without verifying current optimizations active | **BLOCKED** — check cache/timeout/max_tokens first |
| Comparing different intent types | **BLOCKED** — compare like-with-like |
| Attributing to code regression without evidence | **BLOCKED** — GCP-side variance is common |
